###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Compression Technology
Suppose a Chinese character is composed of an $N \times N$ dot matrix pattern of $0$ and $1$, as shown in the figure below. We generate the compression code according to the following rules. A series of consecutive values: starting from the first symbol of the first row of the Chinese character dot matrix pattern, calculate in writing order from top to bottom, from left to right. The first number indicates how many consecutive $0$s there are, the second number indicates how many consecutive $1$s there are next, the third number indicates how many consecutive $0$s there are after that, the fourth number indicates how many consecutive $1$s there are after that, and so on.

For example, the following Chinese character dot matrix pattern:

```
0001000
0001000
0001111
0001000
0001000
0001000
1111111
```

The corresponding compression code is: `7 3 1 6 1 6 4 3 1 6 1 6 1 3 7` (the first number is $N$, the remaining digits represent alternating $0$ and $1$ counts, and the compression code guarantees $N \times N=\text{the sum of alternating digits}$)

### Input Format

Chinese character dot matrix pattern (no spaces between dot matrix symbols). ($3\le N\le 200$)

### Output Format

One line, compression code.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'zip.in' and write the output to a file named 'zip.out'.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
char str[40005] = {0};
int main() {
    freopen("zip.in", "r", stdin);
    freopen("zip.out", "w", stdout);
    int len;
    for (len = 0; cin >> str[len]; len++); 
    len--;
    cout << (int)sqrt(len) + 1 << " ";
    int tmp = 0;
    char a = '0';
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        if (str[i] == a) tmp++;
        else {
            cout << tmp << " ";
            a = str[i];
            tmp = 1;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
string str, tmp;
int main() {
    freopen("zip.in", "r", stdin);
    freopen("zip.out", "w", stdout);
    while (cin >> tmp) {
        str += tmp;
    }
    cout << round(sqrt(str.size())) << " ";
    char a = '0';
    int temp = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < str.size(); i++) {
        if (str[i] == a) temp++;
        else {
            cout << temp << " ";
            a = str[i];
            temp = 1;
        }
    }
    cout << temp << endl;
    return 0;
}
```

