### Input format

The first line of the input contains an integer $t$ ($1\le t\le 100$), indicating the number of test cases.

For the next $t$ groups of data, the first line of each group contains a number $n$ ($1\le n\le 1000$), indicating the number of nodes in the tree.

Then $n-1$ lines, each line containing two numbers $x$ and $y$ ($0\lt x,y\lt n$), representing that $y$ is the child node of $x$, separated by a space.

### Output format

