###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Talent Show

Mr. Garlic participated in a talent show audition with the following rules:

  * The audition lasts for a total of $x$ hours. (If the last person starts performing at or before $x$ hours, the judges will watch the performance before leaving.)

  * The judges have limited patience. If someone performs too poorly, they will be driven off the stage immediately, and that time can be ignored.

Now given the **name** and **duration** of each registered program, following the principle of first come, first perform, can Mr. Garlic have the opportunity to showcase his talents?

Note: Mr. Garlic's performance is: $kaomianjin$.

### Input Format

In the first line, input the first positive integer $x(1 \le x \le 100)$, representing the total audition time. (In **hours** unit, the unit for expressing time below is **not exactly the same**)

There are several lines following, with the end of the file as the ending.

Each line first inputs a string with a length not exceeding $100$. If the string is "tingtingting", it means that the previous contestant was driven off the stage; if the string is not, it represents the program name, and then input an integer $t$ to indicate the program duration (in **minutes** unit, a positive integer not exceeding $15$).

The number of lines does not exceed $10^4$.

### Output Format

If Mr. Garlic did not get the opportunity to showcase his talents, output "Unfortunately."; if Mr. Garlic successfully showcased his talents, output "Congratulations!"; if Mr. Garlic was directly driven off the stage, output "Hahaha." (Output does not include quotation marks)

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
#include<vector>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    string trl="Unfortunately.";
    int x;
    vector<string>s;
    vector<int>time;
    int i=1;
    string s1;
    cin>>x;
    while(cin>>s1){
        s.push_back(s1);
        if(s1!="tingtingitng"){
            int a;
            cin>>a;
            time.push_back(a);
        }
        i++;
    }i=0;
    while(x>0){
        if(i!=0&&s[i]=="tingtingting"){
            x-=time[i-1];
            if(s[i]=="kaomianjin"){
                trl="Hahaha.";
                break;
            }
        }else if(i!=s[i].size()-1&&s[i+1]!="tingtingting"){
            if(s[i]=="kaomianjin"){
                trl="Congratulations!";
                break;
            }
        }
        i++;
    }cout<<trl<<endl;
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
#include<vector>
using namespace std;
vector<int>v;
int main(){
    string s;int b;
    int t,allt,sum=0;
    cin>>allt;
    allt*=60;
    while(cin>>s){
        if(s=="tingtingting"){
            v.pop_back();
            sum=v[v.size()-1];

        }else if(s=="kaomianjin"){
            cin>>t;
            if(cin>>s&&s=="tingtingting"){
                cout<<"Hahaha."<<endl;
                return 0;
            }
            cout<<"Congratulations!"<<endl;
            return 0;
        }else{
            cin>>t;
            sum+=t;
            if(sum>=allt)break;
            v.push_back(sum);
        }
    }
    cout<<"Unfortunately."<<endl;
    return 0;
}
```

###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Noble Shops
On a noble street, there are $N$ noble shops, each selling a noble product.

The noble price of the noble product sold in the $i$-th noble shop is $p_i$, and its value is $v_i$. However, the noble clerk will also put forward a noble requirement: "Please do not step into this shop if you have less than $q_i$ on you."

Mr. Garlic, who is not so noble, has a total of $M$ dollars. He wants to know the maximum value of noble products he can buy?

### Input Format

In the first line, input two numbers $N, M$.

In the next $N$ lines, input $3$ numbers in each line, $p_i, v_i, q_i$ represent the price of the $i$-th noble product, the value of the $i$-th noble product, and the restriction of the $i$-th noble shop on customers.

$1\leq N, M, p_i, v_i, q_i\leq 5000$, where $p_i \leq q_i$.

### Output Format

Output an integer, representing the maximum value of noble products Mr. Garlic can buy.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'noble.in' and write the output to a file named 'noble.out'.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <cstring>
#include <algorithm>
using namespace std;
int dp[5010];

int w[5005], c[5005],q[5005];

int main() {
    freopen("noble.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("noble.out","w",stdout);
    int N, V;
    cin >> N >> V;
    for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
        cin >> w[i] >> c[i] >> q[i];
    }
    int flag = 1;
    for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
        for(int j = V; j >= c[i];j--){
            if(q[i] <= j)
            dp[j] = max(dp[j],dp[j-c[i]]+w[i]);
        }
    }
    cout<<dp[V]<<endl;
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int dp[5010];

int w[5005], c[5005],q[5005];

int main() {
    freopen("noble.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("noble.out","w",stdout);
    int N, V;
    cin >> N >> V;
    for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
        cin >> w[i] >> c[i] >> q[i];
    }
    int mx = 1000000000,mxi;
    for(int i = 1;i < N;i ++){
        mx = 1000000000;
    	for(int j = i;j <= N;j ++){
    		if( q[j] - w[j] < mx){
    			mx = q[j] - w[j];
    			mxi = j;
			}
		}
    	swap(q[i],q[mxi]);
    	swap(w[i],w[mxi]);
    	swap(c[i],c[mxi]);
	}
    for (int i = 0; i <= N; i++) {
        for(int j = V; j >= q[i];j--){

            dp[j] = max(dp[j],dp[j-w[i]]+c[i]);
        }
    }



    cout<<dp[V]<<endl;
    return 0;
}
```

