It is known that all number plates have been announced. Can you help Mr. Garlic calculate which number he is in the order of claiming the souvenirs?

### Input Format

The input has $n$ lines. The first line is a positive integer: $n(1 \le n \le 10000)$, the number of announced number plates.

The following $n$ lines, each line is a string of numbers with a length of no more than $10$, which is the number on each number plate. The last string of numbers is the information on Mr. Garlic's number plate.

### Output Format

Output a line, indicating the number of Mr. Garlic's claim for the souvenir.

