Problem Description:
# Program Design T3
Calculate the result of a positive integer plus $2018$.

However, this positive integer is incredibly large, please write a program to help solve it.

### Input Format

Input a positive integer $n(1 \le n \le 10^{1000})$.

### Output Format

Output the result of $n + 2018$.

### Data Range

For $40\%$ of the data, $n\le 10^{19}$. (For this question, you **only need** to complete this part)

For $100\%$ of the data, $n\le 10^{1000}$.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'bigadd.in' and write the output to a file named 'bigadd.out'.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
32767KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include<iostream>
#include<string>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    freopen("bigadd.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("bigadd.out","w",stdout);
    string s;
    int a[1000000],b[4],c[1000005];
    cin>>s;
    int len = s.length();
    for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
        a[len-i] = s[i] - '0';  
    }
    int lenc = 1,x = 0;
    while(lenc<=len){
        c[lenc] = a[lenc]+b[lenc]+x;
        x = c[lenc]/10;
        c[lenc]%=10;
        lenc++;
    }
    for(int i=lenc;i>=1;i--){
        cout<<c[i];
    }
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include<iostream>
#include<string>
using namespace std;

int a[1005];

int main(){
    freopen("bigadd.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("bigadd.out","w",stdout);
    string num;
    cin>>num;
    int len;
    len = num.size();
    for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
        a[i] = num[len-1-i]-'0';
    }
    a[0]+=2018;
    for(int i=0;i<len;i++){
        a[i+1]+=a[i]/10;
        a[i]%=10;
    }
    while(a[len]){
        a[len+1]+=a[len]/10;
        a[len]%=10;
        len++;
    }
    for(int i=len-1;i>=0;i--){
        cout<<a[i];
    }
    return 0;
}
```

