Cauliflower Girl has prepared $n$ sets of data. Please help Mr. Garlic find the set with the largest difference. If there are multiple sets with the same largest difference, output the set with the smaller minimum number. If the minimum numbers are the same, output the set that was inputted earlier.

### Input Format

The first line inputs an integer $N(1 \le N \le 100)$, indicating there are $N$ sets of data. The following $N$ lines each input two integers $X(1 \le X \le 20)$ and $Y(1 \le Y \le 20)$.

### Output Format

Output the set with the largest difference. If there are multiple sets with the same largest difference, output the set with the smaller minimum number.

**Hints:**

  * ① The difference must be a non-negative number;
  * ② To convert it into a problem of finding the maximum value, we need to pay attention to how we select a set that meets the condition `the one with the smaller minimum number` when there are multiple maximum values.

