Problem Description:
# Decrypting Passwords (Optional)
Alice and Bob want to transmit a piece of information, but they don't want anyone other than themselves to know, so they come up with an encryption method. First, specify the number of times $n(1 \le n \le 9)$, then output the content in parentheses $n$ times, such as `2(ab)`, then output `abab`. The content in parentheses can be nested, such as `3(a(2(b)))`, then output `abbabbabb`.

### Input Format

Input a string $s$, representing the encrypted ciphertext.

### Output Format

Output the translated instructions.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
32767KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    string s,ans="";
    cin>>s;
    stack<char> v;
    for(int i=0;i<s.size();i++){
        string temp="",x="";
        if(s[i]!=')'){
            v.push(s[i]);
        }else{
            while(v.top()!='('){
                temp+=v.top();
                v.pop();
            }
            reverse(temp.begin(),temp.end());
            if(v.size()!=0&&v.top()>='0'&&v.top()<='9'){
                int num=v.top()-'a';
                for(int j=1;j<=num;j++){
                    x+=temp;
                }
                v.pop();
            }
            if(v.size()!=0&&v.top()=='('&&s[i+1]==')'){
                v.pop();
                i++;
            }
            for(int j=0;j<x.size();j++){
                v.push(x[j]);
            }
        }
    }
    while(v.size()){
        ans+=v.top();
        v.pop();
    }
    reverse(ans.begin(),ans.end());
    cout<<ans;
    return 0;
}
```
