Problem Description:
# Align Output
To see the output more clearly and neatly, we can control the output format.

Read in three integers and output them right-aligned with each integer occupying an 8-character width.

#### Input Format

There is only one line, containing three integers within the `int` range, separated by a single space.

#### Output Format

There is only one line, output the three integers in the required format, separated by a single space.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
65535KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <cstring>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    int a,b,c,as,bs,cs;
    cin>>a>>b>>c;
    int x=1,y=1,z=1;
    as=a,bs=b,cs=c;
    while(a>0){
        a/=10;
        x++;
    }
    while(b>0){
        b/=10;
        y++;
    }
    while(c>0){
        c/=10;
        z++;
    }
    for(int i=0;i<8-x;i++){
        cout<<" ";
    }
    cout<<as;
    for(int i=0;i<8-y;i++){
        cout<<" ";
