Problem Description:
# Program Design T3
Calculate the result of a positive integer plus $2018$.

However, this positive integer is incredibly large, please write a program to help solve it.

### Input Format

Input a positive integer $n(1 \le n \le 10^{1000})$.

### Output Format

Output the result of $n + 2018$.

### Data Range

For $40\%$ of the data, $n\le 10^{19}$. (For this question, you **only need** to complete this part)

For $100\%$ of the data, $n\le 10^{1000}$.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'bigadd.in' and write the output to a file named 'bigadd.out'.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
32767KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <cstdio>
using namespace std;
int a[1005] = {0};
int main() {
    freopen("bigadd.in", "r", stdin);
    freopen("bigadd.out", "w", stdout);
    string num;
    int len;
    len = num.size();
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        a[i] = num[len - 1 - i] - '0';
    }
    a[0] += 2018;
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        a[i + 1] += a[i] / 10;
        a[i] %= 10;
    }
    while (a[len]) {
        a[len + 1] += a[len] / 10;
        a[len] %= 10;
        len++;
    }
    for (int i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) { 
        cout << a[i];
    }
    fclose(stdin);
    fclose(stdout);
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <cstdio>
using namespace std;
int a[1005] = {0};
int main() {
    freopen("bigadd.in", "r", stdin);
    freopen("bigadd.out", "w", stdout);
    string num;
    cin >> num;
    int len;
    len = num.size();
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        a[i] = num[len - 1 - i] - '0';
    }
    a[0] += 2018;
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        a[i + 1] += a[i] / 10;
        a[i] %= 10;
    }
    while (a[len]) {
        a[len + 1] += a[len] / 10;
        a[len] %= 10;
        len++;
    }
    for (int i = len - 1; i >= 0; i--) { 
        cout << a[i];
    }
    fclose(stdin);
    fclose(stdout);
    return 0;
}
```

