###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Foodie Mr. Garlic

Mr. Garlic is a foodie, and today he has a big appetite. He goes to a restaurant with abundant dishes for dinner. There are a total of $n$ dishes in the restaurant, and Mr. Garlic wants to eat $m$ dishes, only eating each dish once. To get the purest taste, he decides to finish one dish before starting the next one.

Mr. Garlic will get $a_i$ satisfaction points for eating the $i$-th dish. The restaurant also provides Mr. Garlic with $k$ suggestions. The $i$-th suggestion is that if Mr. Garlic eats dish $x_i$ immediately after dish $y_i$, he will get an additional $c_i$ satisfaction points.

Mr. Garlic wants to know which dishes to choose and in what order to eat them to maximize his satisfaction. He wants you to tell him the maximum satisfaction he can get.

### Input format

The first line contains three integers $n, m, k(1 \leq m \leq n \leq 18, 0 \leq k \leq n \times (n - 1))$.

The second line contains $n$ integers $a_i(0 \leq a_i \leq 10 ^ 9)$.

The following $k$ lines, each with three integers $x_i, y_i, c_i(1 \leq x_i, y_i \leq n, 0 \leq c_i \leq 10 ^ 9)$.

It is guaranteed that for different suggestions $i, j$, there will be no situation where $x_i = x_j$ and $y_i = y_j$.

### Output format

Output one line containing an integer, representing the maximum satisfaction Mr. Garlic can get.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'meal.in' and write the output to a file named 'meal.out'.

### Time Limit
2000ms

### Memory Limit
262144KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int n,m,k,x,y,c,ans=0;
int dp[1<<18][25];
int vis[25][25],a[25];
int count(int x){
	int cnt=0;
	while(x){
		cnt+=x&1;
		x>>=1;
	}
	return cnt;
}
int main(){
    freopen("meal.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("meal.out","w",stdout);
	cin>>n>>m>>k;
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		cin>>a[i];
	}
	for(int i=1;i<=k;i++){
		cin>>x>>y>>c;
		vis[x][y]=c;
	}
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		dp[1<<i][i]=a[i];
	}
	for(int i=0;i<(1<<n);i++){
		for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
			if(i&(1<<j)){
				for(int k=0;k<n;k++){
					if(i&(1<<k))
						dp[i|(1<<j)][j]=dp[i][k]+a[i]+vis[k][j];
				}
			}
		}
	}
	for(int i=0;i<(1<<n);i++){
		if(count(i)==m){
			for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
				ans=max(ans,dp[i][j]);
			}
		}
	}
	cout<<ans;
	return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;
int n,m,k,x,y,c;
long long ans=0;
long long dp[1<<18][25];
long long vis[25][25],a[25];
int count(int x){
	int cnt=0;
	while(x){
		cnt+=x&1;
		x>>=1;
	}
	return cnt;
}
int main(){
    freopen("meal.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("meal.out","w",stdout);
	cin>>n>>m>>k;
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		cin>>a[i];
	}
	for(int i=1;i<=k;i++){
		cin>>x>>y>>c;
		vis[x-1][y-1]=c;
	}
	for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
		dp[1<<i][i]=a[i];
	}
	for(int i=0;i<(1<<n);i++){
		for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
			if(!(i&(1<<j))){
				for(int k=0;k<n;k++){
					if(i&(1<<k))
						dp[i|(1<<j)][j]=max(dp[i|(1<<j)][j],dp[i][k]+a[j]+vis[k][j]);
				}
			}
            if(count(i|(1<<j))==m){
                ans=max(ans,dp[i|(1<<j)][j]);
            }
		}
	}
	cout<<ans;
	return 0;
}
```

