# Elevator
Recently, Mr. Garlic has mysteriously become the "elevator administrator," responsible for controlling the elevator's movements.

It is known that the elevator takes $5$ seconds to rise one floor, $4$ seconds to descend one floor, $3$ seconds to open the door, and $2$ seconds for each person to exit the elevator. Closing the door takes no time.

Mr. Garlic controls the elevator starting from the $0$th floor. At this time, $n$ people will enter the elevator, and each person will tell Mr. Garlic the floor they want to go to. Now, Mr. Garlic wants to calculate the total time the elevator needs to run for this trip.

Note that the elevator must return to the $0$th floor in the end.

### Input format

The input consists of two lines. The first line contains a positive integer $n$, representing the number of people.

The second line contains $n$ positive integers, where $a_i$ represents the floor that the $i$th person wants to go to.

### Output format

Output one line, an integer, which is the answer.

### Data range

$1 \leq n \leq 10 ^ 5, 1 \leq a_i \leq 10 ^ {12}$.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'elevator.in' and write the output to a file named 'elevator.out'.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

