###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Number Plates

Mr. Garlic has won the chance to receive a limited edition Disney souvenir for free. However, since the value of the souvenirs varies, everyone who has won the chance to receive one needs to claim them in a certain order.

It is known that when each person gets the free claim qualification, they will randomly draw a string of numbers, and the order of the claim qualification is related to this string of numbers. The order is defined as follows: sort by the sum of all the numbers in the string in ascending order, and when the sum of the numbers is equal, the larger the value represented by the string of numbers, the higher the priority.

It is known that all number plates have been announced. Can you help Mr. Garlic calculate which number he is in the order of claiming the souvenirs?

### Input Format

The input has $n$ lines. The first line is a positive integer: $n(1 \le n \le 10000)$, the number of announced number plates.

The following $n$ lines, each line is a string of numbers with a length of no more than $10$, which is the number on each number plate. The last string of numbers is the information on Mr. Garlic's number plate.

### Output Format

Output a line, indicating the number of Mr. Garlic's claim for the souvenir.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
32767KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <stdio.h>
#include <algorithm>
#include <ctime>
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

long long a[10000];

bool cmp(long long x,long long y)
{
    long long k=x,l=y,sum1=0,sum2=0;
    while(k!=0)
    {
        sum1+=k%10;
        k/=10;
    }
    while(l!=0)
    {
        sum2+=l%10;
        l/=10;
    }
    if(sum1!=sum2)
    {
        return sum1<sum2; 
    }
    else
    {
        return x>y;
    }
}

int main()
{
    long long n,fds;
    cin>>n;
    for(long long i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        cin>>a[i];
    }
    fds=a[n-1];
    sort(a,a+1,cmp);
    for(long long j=0;j<n;j++)
    {
        if(a[j]==fds)
        {
            cout<<j<<endl;
            return 0;
        }
    }
}
```
