Output a line of numbers $a_0$, $a_1$, $\cdots$, $a_n$, separated by a comma and a space. These numbers represent all the positions visited by the game piece, starting from the initial position and ending when the game ends. The last position visited, which is the position that leads to the game's end, should also be included, even if it was visited before. There should not be a comma at the end. (The given data guarantees that the answer will not exceed the range of a `long long int`).

