###Instruction:
Problem Description:
# Talent Show

Mr. Garlic participated in a talent show audition with the following rules:

  * The audition lasts for a total of $x$ hours. (If the last person starts performing at or before $x$ hours, the judges will watch the performance before leaving.)

  * The judges have limited patience. If someone performs too poorly, they will be driven off the stage immediately, and that time can be ignored.

Now given the **name** and **duration** of each registered program, following the principle of first come, first perform, can Mr. Garlic have the opportunity to showcase his talents?

Note: Mr. Garlic's performance is: $kaomianjin$.

### Input Format

In the first line, input the first positive integer $x(1 \le x \le 100)$, representing the total audition time. (In **hours** unit, the unit for expressing time below is **not exactly the same**)

There are several lines following, with the end of the file as the ending.

Each line first inputs a string with a length not exceeding $100$. If the string is "tingtingting", it means that the previous contestant was driven off the stage; if the string is not, it represents the program name, and then input an integer $t$ to indicate the program duration (in **minutes** unit, a positive integer not exceeding $15$).

The number of lines does not exceed $10^4$.

### Output Format

If Mr. Garlic did not get the opportunity to showcase his talents, output "Unfortunately."; if Mr. Garlic successfully showcased his talents, output "Congratulations!"; if Mr. Garlic was directly driven off the stage, output "Hahaha." (Output does not include quotation marks)

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    vector<string> name;
    vector<int> min;
    int t,tot = 0;
    cin >> t;
    t *= 60;
    string x;
    int i = 0;
    while(cin >> x) {
        name.push_back(x);    
        if(x != "tingtingting") {
            int time;
            cin >> time;
            min.push_back(time);
            tot += time;
        }
    }
    for(i = 0;i < name.size();i++) {
        if(x == "kaomianjin") {
            if(name[i+1] == "tingtingting") cout << "Hahaha.";
            else if(tot <= t) cout << "Congratulations!";            
            else cout << "Unfortunately.";           
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    vector<string> name;
    vector<int> min;
    int t,tot = 0;
    cin >> t;
    t *= 60;
    string x;
    int i = 0;
    while(cin >> x) {
        if(x != "tingtingting") {
            name.push_back(x);   
            int time;
            cin >> time;
            tot += time;
            min.push_back(tot);         
        } else {
           if (name[name.size()-1]=="kaomianjin") {
               if(tot > t) {
                 cout << "Unfortunately.";
               } else {
                  cout << "Hahaha.";
               }
                return 0;
            }
            tot -= min[min.size()-1];
            name.pop_back();
        }
    }
    for(i = 0;i < name.size();i++) {
        x = name[i];        
        if(x == "kaomianjin") {
            if(name[i+1] == "tingtingting") cout << "Hahaha.";
            else if(min[i] <= t) cout << "Congratulations!";     
            else cout << "Unfortunately.";           
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

