Problem Description:
# Find the Longest Word
For a given English sentence, find the longest English word in it.

### Input Format

The input only has one line, which is an English sentence with spaces but no punctuation marks.

### Output Format

Output the longest English word in the sentence. If there are multiple words with the same length, output the first one that appears.

### Time Limit
1000ms

### Memory Limit
262144KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int a = 0, index = 0;
    string s;
    getline(cin, s);
    for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        if (s[i] == ' ') {
            a = 0;
        } else {
            a++;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```
### Response:
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int a = 0, b = 0, c = 0, index = 0;
    string s;
    getline(cin, s);
    for (int i = 0; i < s.size(); i++) {
        if (s[i] == ' ') {
            a = 0;
            index = i + 1;
            continue;
        } else {
            a++;
        }
        if (a > b) {
            b = a;
            c = index;
        }
    }
    for (int i = 0; i < b; i++) {
        cout << s[c + i];
    }
    return 0;
}
```

