Problem Description:
# Maximum Submatrix
Given an $n \times m$ matrix $A$, find a non-empty submatrix in $A$ such that the sum of its elements is maximized.

### Input Format

The first line of the input contains two integers $n, m (1 \leq n, m \leq 50)$, representing the number of rows and columns of matrix $A$. The following $n$ lines, each with $m$ integers, represent the matrix $A_{i,j}(-1000 \leq A_{i,j} \leq 1000)$. Adjacent numbers are separated by a space.

### Output Format

Output one line containing a single integer, representing the sum of elements in the largest submatrix in $A$.

Your program should use file input and output. Read the input from a file named 'submatrix.in' and write the output to a file named 'submatrix.out'.

### Time Limit
2000ms

### Memory Limit
131072KB

This is an incorrect code to the problem:
```c++
#include<iostream>
#include<cmath>
#include<cstdio>
#include<string>
using namespace std;
int main(){
    freopen("submatrix.in","r",stdin);
    freopen("submatrix.out","w",stdout);
    short a,b;
    cin>>a>>b;
    int aa[259][51];
    for(int i=0;i<a;i++){
        for(int j=0;j<b;j++){
            cin>>aa[i][j];
        }
    }
    int max=-100000;
    int sum=0;
    for(int i=0;i<a;i++){
        for(int j=i;j<a;j++){
            for(int k=0;k<b;k++){
                for(int l=k;l<b;l++){
                    sum=0;
                    for(int p=i;p<j;p++){
                        for(int q=k;q<l;q++){
                            sum+=aa[p][q];
                        }
                    }
                    if(sum>max){
                        max=sum;
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    cout<<max<<endl;
    return 0;

}
```
