# I Want to Stay Healthy Today

After studying hard for an entire afternoon, Mr. Garlic is going to the cafeteria for dinner. The school cafeteria always provides free rice and soup. Therefore, Mr. Garlic only needs to worry about what dishes to eat every day. As a health-conscious young man, Mr. Garlic believes that for dinner, **one can skip meat dishes, but must eat vegetarian dishes**.

The cafeteria offers a total of $N$ vegetarian dishes, each with a price $p_i$ and a deliciousness value $v_i$; and $M$ meat dishes, each with a price $q_i$ and a deliciousness value $w_i$.

Mr. Garlic has $X$ yuan left for living expenses today, and he wants to know the maximum deliciousness value he can achieve for this sumptuous and healthy dinner.

### Input Format

In the first line, input three positive integers $N,M,X$.

In the second line, input $N$ numbers, $p_1, p_2, \cdots, p_N$, representing the prices of vegetarian dishes.

In the third line, input $N$ numbers, $v_1, v_2, \cdots, v_N$, representing the deliciousness values of vegetarian dishes.

In the fourth line, input $M$ numbers, $q_1, q_2, \cdots, q_M$, representing the prices of meat dishes.

In the fifth line, input $M$ numbers, $w_1, w_2, \cdots, w_M$, representing the deliciousness values of meat dishes.

$1\leq N , M \leq 100,1\leq X, p_i, q_i\leq 5000,\ 1\leq v_i,w_i \leq 100000$.

### Output Format

Output a single integer, the maximum deliciousness value that meets the requirements of the problem.

