# Annoying Queue Jumping

Mr. Garlic was in line to receive welfare today but found that there were many uncivilized people who were cutting in line.

He noticed that if a person joining the queue had a friend in the line, they would stand behind their friend (if they had multiple friends, they would stand behind their first friend); if they had no friends, they could only stand at the end of the line. People with the same first letter of their names are considered friends (e.g., Alice and Amy are friends, while Alice and Bob are not friends). Please simulate this queuing process.

### Input Format

Input a positive integer $n(1 \le n \le 100)$, representing the number of operations;

